description: RU a new Spring '26 student who either recently enrolled in or is considering adding Douglass to your Rutgers experience? Douglass, historically known as the women's college at Rutgers, provides students with staff and peer mentors to help you hit the ground running. Douglass also focuses on women's leadership by providing special opportunities for you to build your skills and surround yourself with like-minded students who are passionate about social justice and centering women's lived experiences.  At this event you will meet other new Douglass students, staff and current/experienced Douglass students who can give you insight into the opportunities and experiences that will enhance your college journey while building your resume and support circle. From social events like International Women's Day to internship and research opportunities, Douglass can add an additional layer of support and enhancement to any major.
name: Douglass Residential College Facts & Snacks
